<img class="aligncenter wp-image-565" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/peru-national-football-team-300x183.jpg" alt="" width="542" height="331" />

<strong><u>World Cup Qualifier South America</u></strong>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Peru played a total of 18 games for their qualifying round in South America with a total of 26 points in the qualifying table securing the fifth position in the table. The country conceded 7 wins, 5 draws and 6 losses during their qualifying rounds. Peru defeated 1-0 against Paraguay in the third round, in which Jefferson Farfan scored the net in 19 minutes. Peru great performance against Bolivia in 7<sup>th</sup> round earned them 3 points in which they scored thrice and they won 2-1 against Ecuador in the 8<sup>th</sup> round. In the 11<sup>th</sup> round, Paraguay lost 1-4 to Peru and in the 14<sup>th</sup> round, they win 2-1 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/uruguay-road-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Uruguay</a>. Peru defeated Bolivia in the 15<sup>th</sup> round and Ecuador lost 1-2 against Peru in the 16<sup>th</sup> round. Peru drew last two games against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/argentina-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Argentina</a> and <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/colombia-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Colombia</a> in 17<sup>th</sup> and 18<sup>th</sup> round respectively. After finishing 4<sup>th</sup> in the South American qualifying group, Peru was advance to the intercontinental play-offs against New Zealand. Peru drew 0-0 against New Zealand in Wellington on 11 November but reached the FIFA World Cup 2018 by defeating New Zealand on aggregate as the Peru team scored a brace in Lima.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-566" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/peru-celebration-300x204.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="374" />

